cepted those missionaries who treated them with sensitivity and respect and integrated Christian beliefs and practices into their established belief system. Today, a blend of Christian and Ojibwa ideas is still interwoven in the lives of Berens River residents, with both traditions holding meaning and sincerity. Their uniquely adaptive religion sheds new light on our understanding of cultural contact and conversion, placing the indigenous experience of these events at centre stage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBerens River Valley (Man.) -- History. 0aCatholic Church -- Missions -- Manitoba -- Berens River Valley -- History. 0aElectronic books. 0aMethodist Church -- Missions -- Manitoba -- Berens River Valley -- History. 0aMethodist ChurchxMissionszManitobazBerens River ValleyxHistory. 0aOjibwa Indians -- Manitoba -- Berens River Valley -- History. 0aOjibwa Indians -- Manitoba -- Berens River Valley -- Religion. 0aOjibwa Indians -- Missions -- Manitoba -- Berens River Valley -- History. 0aOjibwa IndiansxMissionszManitobazBerens River ValleyxHistory. 0aOjibwa IndianszManitobazBerens River ValleyxHistory. 0aOjibwa IndianszManitobazBerens River ValleyxReligion. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology of Religion.2bisacsh1 aMcKay, Stan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781552383698?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781552383698423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781552383698/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Packa